Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) and @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the @lemon{1}(zested). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). In a #small bowl{}, mix together the herbs, @Chermoula Spice Mix{1}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and half the garlic and lemon zest. Lay the @coley fillet{2} on a #plate{}, season both sides with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then spread the chermoula mix on top of each fillet.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Preheat the #oven{} to 180°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil. Once boiling, stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2} to dissolve, then stir in the @freekeh{100%g}. Bring back to the boil and reduce to a simmer until the grains have doubled in size and are tender enough to eat, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{} and return to the pan off the heat with the lid on to keep warm.

In the meantime, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and sliced). Trim, then grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and grated) on a #coarse grater{} (no need to peel).

Heat a glug of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Pop the onion into the pan, along with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and a good pinch of salt. Cook until soft and beginning to colour, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once softened, increase the heat slightly then stir in the carrot. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Mix the veggies into the cooked freekeh along with the remaining lemon zest.

As the veggies are cooking, drizzle a little oil onto a #baking tray{} and place the coley fillets on top. Halve the lemon, then thinly slice one half into rounds. Lay one slice of lemon on top of each fillet then cook on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when the flesh is opaque and flaky.

Meanwhile, in another small bowl, mix together the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste with juice from the remaining lemon and some salt and pepper. Just before serving, carefully mix the @wild rocket{40%g} into the freekeh, taste and season with salt and pepper as required. Divide the freekeh salad between your plates and when the fish is ready, pop a fillet on top and drizzle over the yogurt dressing. Delicious!